[2] Bangladesh (Chittagong)
Date: 13 Nov 2003
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Daily Star, Bangladesh Tue 11 Nov 2003 [edited]
<http://www.thedailystar.net/2003/11/11/d3111101066.htm>

Dengue is back in the port city, already claiming one life and attacking
many more, after a major outbreak about 2 years ago. A young housewife died
of dengue at Chittagong Medical College Hospital (CMCH) on Sunday, and 5
other dengue patients including a doctor are under treatment, hospital
sources said. A number of dengue patients were reported to be admitted to
private hospitals and clinics and many visited private medical
practitioners for treatment. Sultanul Alam said dengue spread with the
proliferation of Aedes mosquitoes following recent rains in the city.
Spraying of insecticides at breeding grounds for mosquitoes will be geared up.
[Byline: Nurul Alam]
