[4] India (New Delhi)
Date: Wed, 12 Nov 2003 07:48:35 -0800 (PST)
From: Marianne Hopp <mjhopp12@yahoo.com>
Source: WHO Outbreak News Dengue fever in India - update [edited]
<http://www.who.int/csr/don/2003_11_12/en/>

From 1 Jun to 9 Nov 2003, 2185 laboratory-confirmed cases of dengue fever
have been reported in Delhi and surrounding areas (see previous report
<http://www.who.int/csr/don/2003_10_30/en/>).
Additional information is being sought to identify possible cases of dengue
haemorrhagic fever. Circulating dengue virus serotypes DEN-3 and 2 have
been reported to be associated with this outbreak. The outbreak is ongoing
and vector control measures have been intensified.
******
[5] India (Maharashtra)
Date: 13 Nov 2003
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Express News Service, Pune Newsline 9 Nov 2003 [edited]
<http://cities.expressindia.com/fullstory.php?newsid=67616>

Dengue continues to stalk us, with 175 persons affected so far. 5 deaths
have been reported from the city, while Pimpri-Chinchwad registered 3.
